top.value: Providing medical services in the field of combating blindness and the diseases that cause it to beneficiaries with low incomes who cannot cover the costs of their treatment.
Health education for everyone receiving treatment . Providing patients' needs for medicines, glasses and lenses . Subsidy from the Ministry of Health of the host country

This campaign comes as part of a series of voluntary medical campaigns to combat blindness and the diseases that cause it, which are funded and implemented by the center in many countries around the world.

Performing specialized surgeries. Providing patients' needs for medicines, glasses and lenses as needed. Removing the suffering of many blind people. Health education for everyone receiving treatment for prevention. Subsidy from the Ministry of Health in the beneficiary country that suffers from a shortage of ophthalmologists
800 cases were detected, 400 cataract operations were performed, 400 glasses, medicines and eye drops were distributed
